The paper deals with a graph coloring problem in the context of integrated circuit manufacturing, which suggests a connection to the subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem involves a tree-like structure, which could be related to the subfield of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also presents a dynamic programming algorithm, which is a common technique in the subfield of computational complexity (cs.CC). The application of the algorithm to industrial instances suggests a connection to the subfield of electronic design automation (cs.ETR) and the subfield of engineering and mathematics (cs.EM).
